5/7/22, 23:55 - Amritanshu Raj CR: CONCLUSION
There is no doubt that Indian cinema is a critical and integral part
of Indian culture but It must be a tool for reform and not a tool to
push rhetoric and biases into the minds of millions of innocent
people. Entertainment must not be used as a means to marginalise
women. The role and concept of a hero can be gender neutral if we
all show some broad mindedness. There is no need of portraying
the hero as a masculine beacon. Hero can be anyone irrespective
of their gender. The qualities of heroes must be independent of
gender identity. Showing dominant masculine heroes is equivalent
to promoting patriarchy which has hindered the development and
integration of women in the mainstream world for centuries. The
movies which portray women as central characters could be a
good way to overcome this current trend of masculine heroes. But
the best possible solution of this issue could be the self awareness
of the audience i.e informed citizens build an empowered society.

5/31/22, 21:51 - Sneha Doubt Solver: Dear all,
Greetings from the cultural council! 

Hope you are safe and doing well. The cultural council strongly believes that the feedback from the student community will help us along our journey and is in the interest of all of us. The council carries forward a vision of bringing back the glory of our institute's cultural activities, which were affected by the pandemic. The council is willing to help the students who are eager to learn and would like to take forward their interest and prowess in their interested domains. Thus, considering all these aspects, we are introducing an active feedback system that will be a running form till the end of our tenures and the students have the flexibility to let us know their feedback/ thoughts pertaining to the cultural council/activities/events at any point of time. The council will try its best to take it up and get back to you at the earliest.

Kindly note that the form will be available in each club's Whatsapp group's description and in the sac portal under the cultural section soon apart from this mail for convenient access.

We do believe in feedback and constructive criticism, however, we kindly request you to avoid any personal comments and put forward your feedback and concerns properly and constructively so as to maintain a healthy atmosphere.

We cannot run two caterers currently due to obvious practical and logistic reasons. Once Phase 1B is complete, it will give an option to run two caterers. Also, more in the long run.

Currently mess cuts can be availed three times in a semester provided students should not be in the campus for at least 4 days.

Inspection on the brands, quality of the material, expiry date.... are normally done by the representatives either before the opening of the mess or at the closure time to ensure that the cooking process is not disturbed.  In addition, for the daily inspection of stores and cold rooms, a checklist is being prepared and daily checks will be done by one of the mess committee members in both the campuses.

Only the suggestions that go with the tender agreement are considered. Please don't forget that tender documents abide by the government laws to protect both the clients and service providers. Some permutation combinations are possible. But suggestions like more chicken, unlimited eggs and others are not possible.                 *from today*
                *Until 30/03/2023*
                 *very cold...*

  Remember: Starting tomorrow at 05:27, we will experience the APHELION event.  Earth is at a different distance from the Sun than normal.

 We cannot see this event, but we can feel its impact.  It will last till March.

  We may experience colder weather than usual.

  It can cause fever, cough and difficulty in breathing.
   We should strengthen our immune system by consuming foods that strengthen the lungs and heart.

  The distance from Earth to Sun is 5 light minutes ie 90,000,000km.  Aphelion event takes us 152,000,000  km from the Sun or 66% of the distance.

 Therefore the humidity in the air will increase till the end of March instead of ending in the current month of February due to the south-west monsoon from last July. 
Our body... especially those who feel difficulty in breathing,,
 Older people.. will see a big difference with this coolness.
So we have to keep our health balanced, whether it's cloudy or sunny, the body still feels cold!!!
And winter can cause feelings of lethargy even in healthy people.
Therefore, appropriate changes should be made from the way you dress to the food you eat.
  
 To protect our health... Please share this information with everyone as possible especially family friends who are elderly.  So they might as well be forewarned.
